The paper discusses pruning techniques for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) applications. The paper also discusses the computational complexity and parameter reduction, which are important topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes a general model for pruning techniques, which could be relevant to a wide range of sub-categories in computer science.
